data.title: What famous people are from where your from?
meta_keywords: What famous people are from where your from?
data.meta_description: No one *really, but the town I was originally from is now part of the Fort Smith metropolitan area. So... Rudy Ray Moore who played Dolemite. Laurence
data.text:
Advertisements

No one *really, but the town I was originally from is now part of the Fort Smith metropolitan area. So...

Rudy Ray Moore who played Dolemite.

Laurence Luckinbill who played Spock's half-brother in the dreadful Star Trek V.

And some politicians or football players. Hm kind of disappointing.

Other people from or based in Crawford County, Arkansas include actor Bob Burns and Anti-Catholic cult-leader/sex-offender Tony Alamo. Good times.

*On looking it up I've discovered a Depression-era bank robber is from my hometown.

"The Misfits" (the punk band) is the only "well known" famous people from Lodi, NJ unfortunately (my hometown)

Can't expect much from a suburb.

Some famous people who came from around the area would be James Gandolfini of Westwood (the main guy on The Sopranos), Most of the "Sugar Hill Gang" of Englewood, The Jonas Brothers of Wycoff, Debby Boone of Hackensack...

There's a few from Newark as well such as Queen Latifah, Joe Pesci, Whitney Houston, Redman, Jason Alexander, Ice T, Kat Deluna, Gloria Gaynor, Faith Evans...

There's many others, but I don't want to go too far out of my own area.

Thought I would add to this list for the Santa Rosa, CA area:

Robert Ripley (of Ripley's Believe it or Not) born and raised here.

Charles Schuls (of Peanuts fame) ok not born here but spent the last 40 years of his life here and called it home.

Mark Felt (aka Deep Throat) ok, ok, so not born here he lived here when he died and people found out who he was.

Natalie Wood (ok, only moved here when she was about 2 years old before her acting debut at 4)

Julie London (married to Jack Webb and later to Bobby Troup - known as a pin up girl)

Close by in San Francisco:

Ansel Adams

Bill Bixby

Mel Blanc

Clint Eastwood

Jerry Garcia

Patty Hearst

Steve Jobs

Jack LaLane

Jack London

There's more but I'll let someone else fill in the blanks...

The list is too long, so I'll just post about some people who we personally know or went to school with. Jai Rodriguez from ***** eye for the straight guy went to HS with my sister, and an American Idol finalist from like 4 years ago who came in 5th place is friends with my sister (from our town too). Joe something, forgot his name. Murena I think, something like that.

My sister's landlord was the drummer in the band Alice Cooper. He owns a super huge mansion with an ocean view on Long island. He invited her and her roommates over for the 4th of July. They got to party with the rock stars, pretty cool. Lots of famous people where we are.
